{"id":16490,"date":"2019-01-23T17:45:24","date_gmt":"2019-01-23T12:15:24","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=16490"},"modified":"2019-01-23T18:41:44","modified_gmt":"2019-01-23T13:11:44","slug":"shivakumara-swami","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shivakumara-swami\/","title":{"rendered":"Shivakumara Swami, Wiki, Age, Death, Family, Biography, &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Shivakumara-Swami.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16491\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Shivakumara-Swami.jpg\" alt=\"Shivakumara Swami\" width=\"638\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Shivakumara-Swami.jpg 638w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Shivakumara-Swami-300x235.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 638px) 100vw, 638px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>Shivakumara Swami<\/strong> was an Indian Spiritual leader and Humanitarian. He was the head of the\u00a0Siddaganga Matha\u00a0in\u00a0Karnataka, India and was the founder of Sri Siddaganga Education Society. Swamiji is considered the most respected adherent\u00a0Lingayatism, a sect of Shaivism in Hindu Religion.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce34965405\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce34965405\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shivakumara-swami\/#BiographyWiki\" title=\"Biography\/Wiki\">Biography\/Wiki<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shivakumara-swami\/#Family\" title=\"Family\">Family<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shivakumara-swami\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shivakumara-swami\/#AwardsHonours\" title=\"Awards\/Honours\">Awards\/Honours<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shivakumara-swami\/#Death\" title=\"Death\">Death<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shivakumara-swami\/#Facts\" title=\"Facts\">Facts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"BiographyWiki\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080\">Biography\/Wiki<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Shivakumara Swami was born on 1 April 1907 (<strong>Age: 111 years, 295 days in January 2019<\/strong>) in\u00a0Veerapura, a village near\u00a0Magadi\u00a0in the Kingdom of Mysore (now, in Karnataka). His childhood name was\u00a0Shivanna. When he was eight years old, his mother passed away. He completed his primary education in an Anglo-vernacular school in Nagavalli, a village in\u00a0present-day\u00a0Tumkur district, Karnataka. In 1926, he passed his matriculation. Meanwhile, he was also a student at\u00a0Siddaganga Matha (or Mutt) at Tumkur district in Karnataka. For his higher education, he enrolled at\u00a0Central College of Bangalore to study art and science. He had to drop out of his college, as, he was named the\u00a0successor of Uddana Shivayogi Swami to head the\u00a0Siddaganga Matha (or Mutt).<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_16494\" style=\"width: 650px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-16494\" class=\"size-full wp-image-16494\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg\" alt=\"Shivakumara Swamiji\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Shivakumara-Swamiji-300x169.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-16494\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Shivakumara Swamiji<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080\">Family<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Shivakumara Swami was born to\u00a0Honnegowda (Father) and\u00a0Gangamma (Mother). He was the youngest of all thirteen children of his parents.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080\">Career<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>In\u00a01930, when he was doing his graduation, he was chosen the head of\u00a0Siddaganga Matha or Mutt but did not hold the position until the death of the incumbent head, Shivayogi Swami in 1941. On that occasion, he changed his name from\u00a0Shivanna to Shivakumara. In the same year on 3 March, he entered the monk order, &#8216;viraktashram&#8217; and assumed a pontifical name, Shivkumara Swami.<\/p>\n<p>Throughout his life, Swami laid the foundation of 132 educational institutes. By his philanthropic works, he was respected by all communities. People from all religions, castes, and creeds were helped by his philanthropic activities. He also established some shelter houses and provided food for the poor. In 2007, the Government of Karnataka praised his works and celebrated the centennial birth anniversary of Swamiji. Former President of India, A. P. J. Abdul Kalam also visited Swamiji at Tumkur and hailed the humanitarian and social works of Swamiji.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_16507\" style=\"width: 650px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/A-P-J-Abdul-Kalam-with-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-16507\" class=\"size-full wp-image-16507\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/A-P-J-Abdul-Kalam-with-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg\" alt=\"A. P. J. Abdul Kalam with Shivakumara Swamiji\" width=\"640\" height=\"457\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/A-P-J-Abdul-Kalam-with-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/A-P-J-Abdul-Kalam-with-Shivakumara-Swamiji-300x214.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-16507\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A. P. J. Abdul Kalam with Shivakumara Swamiji<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"AwardsHonours\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080\">Awards\/Honours<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>In 2007,\u00a0Swamiji was given the Karnataka Ratna, the highest civilian award in the state of Karnataka. In 2015, the Government of India bestowed him upon the third highest civilian award of the country, <strong>Padma Bhushan<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_16516\" style=\"width: 650px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Then-Additional-Chief-Secretary-of-the-State-government-V.-Umesh-presented-Padma-Bhushan-award-to-Shivakumara-Swami.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-16516\" class=\"size-full wp-image-16516\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Then-Additional-Chief-Secretary-of-the-State-government-V.-Umesh-presented-Padma-Bhushan-award-to-Shivakumara-Swami.jpg\" alt=\"Then Additional Chief Secretary of the State government, V. Umesh presented Padma Bhushan award to Shivakumara Swami\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Then-Additional-Chief-Secretary-of-the-State-government-V.-Umesh-presented-Padma-Bhushan-award-to-Shivakumara-Swami.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Then-Additional-Chief-Secretary-of-the-State-government-V.-Umesh-presented-Padma-Bhushan-award-to-Shivakumara-Swami-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-16516\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Then Additional Chief Secretary of the State government, V. Umesh presented Padma Bhushan award to Shivakumara Swami<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Death\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080\">Death<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>For the last two or three years, he was suffering from many diseases one after another. On 1 December 2018, he was hospitalised due to liver tube infection. On 8 December, he underwent a gallbladder removal surgery. The same year, on 28 Demeber, he was diagnosed with a lung infection. On 11 January 2019, he was placed on the Life Support as his condition worsened. At 11:44 a.m. on 21st January 2019, he departed this life at the age of 111 years.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_16521\" style=\"width: 650px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Thousands-of-People-during-the-funeral-of-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-16521\" class=\"size-full wp-image-16521\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Thousands-of-People-during-the-funeral-of-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg\" alt=\"Thousands of People during the funeral of Shivakumara Swamiji\" width=\"640\" height=\"463\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Thousands-of-People-during-the-funeral-of-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Thousands-of-People-during-the-funeral-of-Shivakumara-Swamiji-300x217.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-16521\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Thousands of People gathered during the funeral of Shivakumara Swamiji<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"pathway\"><\/div>\n<div class=\"headline\">\n<p>Karnataka govt announced state holiday on 22 January 2019 to mourn Lingayat seer Shivakumara Swamiji&#8217;s death.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Facts\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080\">Facts<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>His other names were; Siddaganga\u00a0Swamijigalu, Nadedaduva Devaru, Kayaka Yogi, Trivida Daasohi, etc.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"headline\">\n<ul>\n<li>His followers and disciples used to call him, &#8216;<strong>Walking God<\/strong>.&#8217; It was also his nickname.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"headline\">\n<ul>\n<li>At the time of his death, he was one of the oldest persons in the country.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"headline\">\n<ul>\n<li>The 14th Prime Minister of India, Narendra Modi, also praised his humanitarian works and visited him in September 2014.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_16525\" style=\"width: 650px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi-meeting-with-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-16525\" class=\"size-full wp-image-16525\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi-meeting-with-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg\" alt=\"Prime Minister Narendra Modi meeting with Shivakumara Swamiji\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi-meeting-with-Shivakumara-Swamiji.jpg 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi-meeting-with-Shivakumara-Swamiji-300x169.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-16525\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Prime Minister Narendra Modi meeting with Shivakumara Swamiji<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Narendra-Modi-offered-condolences-to-Swamiji.png\" \/><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"headline\">\n<ul>\n<li>Congress President, Rahul Gandhi also praised his works and met him in 2018. At the demise of Swamiji, he also offered his condolence.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_16534\" style=\"width: 445px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Rahul-Gandhi-met-Shivakumara-Swamiji-in-2018-in-Karnataka.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-16534\" class=\"size-full wp-image-16534\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Rahul-Gandhi-met-Shivakumara-Swamiji-in-2018-in-Karnataka.jpg\" alt=\"Rahul Gandhi met Shivakumara Swamiji in 2018 in Karnataka\" width=\"435\" height=\"271\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Rahul-Gandhi-met-Shivakumara-Swamiji-in-2018-in-Karnataka.jpg 435w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/Rahul-Gandhi-met-Shivakumara-Swamiji-in-2018-in-Karnataka-300x187.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 435px) 100vw, 435px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-16534\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Rahul Gandhi met Shivakumara Swamiji in 2018 in Karnataka<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\">\n<p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">I am sorry to hear about the passing of Shivakumar Swami Ji, Pontiff of the Siddaganga Mutt. Swami Ji was respected &amp; revered by millions of Indians, from all religions &amp; communities. His passing leaves behind a deep spiritual void. My condolences to all his followers.<\/p>\n<p>&mdash; Rahul Gandhi (@RahulGandhi) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/RahulGandhi\/status\/1087275832756842496?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">January 21, 2019<\/a><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Shivakumara Swami was an Indian Spiritual leader and Humanitarian. He was the head of the\u00a0Siddaganga Matha\u00a0in\u00a0Karnataka, India and was the founder of Sri Siddaganga Education Society. Swamiji is 